{"id": 218, "title": "Ticket #218: Execute nodes should install w/ privsep by default", "description": "<blockquote>\nPriv sep is almost completely happy on execute nodes, so it should become the default install.\n\n<p>They are just a few known long-hanging issues : <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=86\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('86'); return false;\" title='PrivSep chown operation should be \"best-effort\"'>#86</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=88\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('88'); return false;\" title=\"PrivSep Switchboard should provide more detail in error messages\">#88</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=84\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('84'); return false;\" title=\"Condor's init script should start the Master as non-root when PrivSep\">#84</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=107\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('107'); return false;\" title=\"PrivSep: Switchboard's mkdir operation doesn't clean up when it fails\">#107</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=108\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('108'); return false;\" title=\"PrivSep: Switchboard's valid-caller-gids config knob too restrictive\">#108</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=91\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('91'); return false;\" title=\"PrivSep: Create_Process errors do not result in job being held\">#91</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=104\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('104'); return false;\" title=\"GLEXEC_JOB: updating a job's proxy while it's running doesn't work\">#104</a></span>, and <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=105\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('105'); return false;\" title=\"PrivSep: disk usage can be underreported\">#105</a></span>.  Most of these are trivial to fix.  Once these are resolved, we should run in priv sep by default if DAEMON_LIST does not include the schedd.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2010-Aug-27 13:14", "status": "new", "created": "2009-Feb-17 15:28", "fixed_version": "2009-Feb-17 15:28", "broken_version": "v070400", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "", "assigned_to": "zmiller", "derived_from": "", "creator": "tannenba", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}